title: How should Fairmoon move forward?
body:
The Fairmoon community volunteer team now has ownership of the Fairmoon contract but do not control the remaining locked liquidity. Transaction fees remain at 100% right now until the community decides how it wants to move forward. There are a few options:

1. Set a time & date, unlock fees, and let people race to sell their FAIR tokens for whatever little bit they can get.
*earlier sellers will get more than those selling later*

2. Collect existing FAIR tokens by sending to a collection address. That address will sell all of the collected FAIR tokens and airdrop the recovered BNB proportionally to each FAIR holder.

3. Perform a token swap to a new token contract. The new token would be owned by the multisig community treasury and any adjustments would be voted through the community governance process. The contract and use case would need further development and will be decided by follow up community proposals if this is chosen.
choices: 1. Unlock fees and race to sell
